DURBAN - A man was shot dead and his passenger injured during a shooting in Margate, south of Durban, at midday on Wednesday. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said at 12.45pm on Wednesday, Netcare 911 responded to a shooting outside a hardware store off the R620 in Margate. Herbst said reports indicated that an unknown number of gunmen opened fire on the couple sitting in a car in the parking lot. “Medics assessed the scene and found that the adult male driver had sustained fatal injuries after being shot multiple times,” Herbst said. “The adult female passenger sustained a minor graze to her left leg.” Herbst said the woman was treated at the scene. He said the shooting would be investigated. Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said Margate police were investigating a case of murder. “A 33-year-old man was stationary in his vehicle on the national road in Margate near a taxi rank when he was shot by unknown gunman. He sustained multiple gunshot wounds to the upper body and was declared dead at the scene,” Mbele said. Daily News